  "doc_id": "31930",
  "text": "Plasma levels of carotenoids and ␣ -tocopherol were analyzed within a month after blood sample collection. For separation and quantification of ␣ -tocopherol and carotenoids (lutein, zeaxanthin, ␣ -and ␤ -carotene, ␤ -cryptoxanthin and lycopene) a modified reverse-phased HPLC system was used, as previously described [CITATION_1] . Uric acid quantification was carried out on Olympus AU 600 using the Uricase-PAP test (Olympus Europe GmbH, Hamburg, Germany). Plasma antioxidant capacity was determined by a modified Trolox-equivalent antioxidant capacity assay and expressed as Trolox equivalents (TE) as described elsewhere [CITATION_2] .",
